<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>mkimage-server (aka Persus's Shield)</title>
    <style type="text/css">
      body { background-color: #cdcccc; color: #000; font-family: serif; }
      a:visited{color: blue}
      h1, h2, h3, h5 { margin: 0 }
      ul { padding: 0; margin-top: 0}
      li { margin-left: 1.1em; margin-top: 0.2em}
      h5 { font-weight: normal; font-size: x-small}
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <table border=0>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <img src="logo.jpg" alt="logo" />
        </td>
        <td>
          <strong>
            This Server is running
          </strong>
          <h1>
            mkimage-server (aka Persus's Shield)
          </h1>
          <h2>
            A shiny recepie to serve resized images on-the-fly
          </h2>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>
          &nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>
          <ul>
            <li>
            Source image URL is passed as param.
            </li>
            <li>
            URL is checked against a regex to avoid public use.
            </li>
            <li>
            Image is resized using the <a href="http://www.imagemagick.org/">ImageMagick</a> command line tools.
            </li>
            <li>
            Resized image is cached in local directory (configurable).
            </li>
            <li>
            API from <a href="https://github.com/lieldulev/perseus-shield">old</a> version still supported.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <h5>
            Retro on purpose <a
              href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netscape_Navigator">Netscape
              rulez</a>.
          </h5>
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </body>
</html>